column5: Any good spots to share and techniques for fishing lac seul last week of sept. will be fishing out of Fisherman's Cove (south of Ear Falls area) Thanks in advance.

I'll be at Onaway Lodge Sept 16th. Fish the rock humps off Manitoba Point, also called Maniteau Point by some. Fish the "wind" side of islands in the Bay of Islands. A friend of mine just got back today from a fantastic week of fishing Lac Suel.
Thanks Ron. We will be there sept.24th for 4 days. Hope the weather holds. Have you been out to main lake and if so any places to try? We will try Sunlight for one day also. Thanks
We fish Sunlight and Broad every June, but have never needed to go there in September. South Bay inlet is also good late in the year. Good luck. Have a safe trip. Ron
Thanks again. I have been to south inlet. are you fishing islands at top of inlet. If you want would like to talk to you. my email is [email protected].
